The Nature impling is an impling that can be caught in the Impetuous Impulses minigame. They are located throughout Puro-Puro and Gielinor. The player needs at least 58 Hunter to capture this type of impling. Capturing a nature impling will grant the player either 34 (if caught on Puro-Puro) or 36 (if caught elsewhere in Gielinor) Hunter experience, and produces a Nature impling jar.

When the impling is caught, the player can loot the resulting jar to receive an item or trade it with Elnock Inquisitor. The player can either purchase 3 impling jars for one nature impling or, along with 3 essence implings and 2 eclectic implings, purchase a jar generator or fully recharge it if they already own it.

Tip: In the north-west and south-east corners of Puro-Puro are rare impling spawns. "Rare" implings include the following: nature, magpie, ninja and dragon.

Loot[edit | edit source]

At current Grand Exchange prices, opening a nature impling jar gives 3,063 worth of loot, on average. This means opening nature impling jars marks an average profit of −2,800 per jar, however this does not include loot from clue scrolls.

On average, one would profit −279,970 to get a hard clue scroll from nature impling jars at current Grand Exchange prices, excluding the rewards from the completed Treasure Trails.
